    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Lamps that burn olive oil, which is oil extracted from the fruit of the olive tree. They are often characterized by being relatively small, portable, and on the top surface having an opening for adding the oil and a smaller opening from which a wick extends.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
